Package com.CZ2002.project_entities

Class Table

java.lang.Object
com.CZ2002.project_entities.RestaurantEntity
com.CZ2002.project_entities.Table
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class Table extends RestaurantEntity
The Table class represents a dining table at the Restaurant. Each table has a even table size that must lie within bounds defined within Table. A table also has a table number by which it can be uniquely identified.

The Table class is designed to only hold all data related to a table and should not implement any logic in relation to tables.

  • Constructor Details

    • Table

      public Table(int size, int tableNo)
      Constructs a new table that represents a specific table in Restaurant.

      A typical table can have a minimum size of 2 and a maximum size of 10. This constructor does not check if size is within the bounds of a typical table size. The size and tableNo of this table cannot be changed.

      Parameters:
      size - the maximum number of guests that can be seated at this table
      tableNo - the table number that identifies this table
